org.cryptonode.jncryptor
Interface JNCryptor

All Known Implementing Classes:
AES256v2Cryptor
public interface JNCryptor

An JNCryptor encrypts and decrypts data in a proprietary format originally devised by Rob Napier. Use the JNCryptorFactory.getCryptor() method to retrieve a concrete implementation.

An JNCryptor must be threadsafe, as a single instance will be returned from the JNCryptorFactory and potentially shared between threads.

See https://github.com/rnapier/RNCryptor for details on the original implementation in objective-c
